{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3850,"name":"Jimmy Gass","username":"ghidra","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/ghidra/{size}/69_2.png","created_at":"2014-12-31T04:47:02.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eold question:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[quote]i’ve tried:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"viewport\" sizedivisor=\"2 2\" filter=\"false\" format=\"rgba\"/\u0026gt;     \u0026lt;!--or--\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"gbuffer\" sizedivisor=\"2 2\" filter=\"false\" format=\"rgba\"/\u0026gt;       \u0026lt;!--or--\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"viewport\" sizemultiplier=\"0.5 0.5\" filter=\"false\" format=\"rgba\"/\u0026gt;     \u0026lt;!--or--\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"gbuffer\" sizemultiplier=\"0.5 0.5\" filter=\"false\" format=\"rgba\"/\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ebut nothing causes the default renderpath viewport to render at half size.\u003cbr\u003e\nI have successfully, rendered to a half size quad and sampled the texture, but I get antialiasing, even with the filter set to false. Filter set to true i get super aliasing. My desire is to get not aliases, and very crisp colors with no interpolated values.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI guess something that uses GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER and GL_TEXTURE_MAX_FILTER set to GL_NEAREST. (at least that is what this link said \u003ca href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17560335/glsl-render-solid-pixels-without-interpolation-or-antialiasing\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003ehttp://stackoverflow.com/questions/17560335/glsl-render-solid-pixels-without-interpolation-or-antialiasing\u003c/a\u003e without getting into the c++ side of things…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs there a simple way to view fullscreen but still render a very crisp no aliased render.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’ve also tried to change the graphics settings to half my screen resolution then set fullscreen to true. That actually is decent, but what should look like a single pixel looks like a small plus sign.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe best looking results i’ve gotten are from the size divisor, but then I’m getting some color interpolation that i’d rather not have.[/quote]\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:18.107Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":26,"reads":17,"readers_count":16,"score":133.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":707,"topic_slug":"solved-setting-filtermode-to-nearest-was-sizedivisor","display_username":"Jimmy Gass","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17560335/glsl-render-solid-pixels-without-interpolation-or-antialiasing","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"rendering - GLSL render solid pixels, without interpolation.or antialiasing - Stack Overflow","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":109,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":3873,"name":"Jimmy Gass","username":"ghidra","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/ghidra/{size}/69_2.png","created_at":"2015-01-02T18:10:39.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eSo it looks like I just want to set the filter node to “GL_NEAREST”\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI can see in c++ there is a way to set the default filter mode in graphics, however. I dont think I can with angelscript. Also, setting it in C++ to FILTER_NEAREST and setting the renderpath to filter=“true” didnt seem to actually use nearest mode.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf there a way to do this?\u003cbr\u003e\nI dont want the rendering to do any filtering. It would be super cool to just be able to set that on a shader level, or even in the render path for the rendertarget.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks for any help.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:20.168Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":17,"readers_count":16,"score":3.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":707,"topic_slug":"solved-setting-filtermode-to-nearest-was-sizedivisor","display_username":"Jimmy Gass","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":109,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":3874,"name":"","username":"reattiva","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/r/b77776/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-01-02T19:52:54.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eActually when you set “filter=true” you ask for the bilinear filter, instead if you don’t want any filtering on your buffer then you can have the nearest mode by setting “filter=false”.\u003cbr\u003e\nLook at the function: Renderer::GetScreenBuffer\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:20.288Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":17,"readers_count":16,"score":3.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":707,"topic_slug":"solved-setting-filtermode-to-nearest-was-sizedivisor","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":72,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":3876,"name":"Jimmy Gass","username":"ghidra","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/ghidra/{size}/69_2.png","created_at":"2015-01-02T22:00:39.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI see, it does in fact.\u003cbr\u003e\nWhen I render to a sizedivisor 2 2 buffer, i’m getting half values or what look like interpolated values. Which is not desireable for what I am doing. I’ll have to look into another way. Thanks for point that out.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo then it might be applyig a filter when I sample a half sized rendertarget.\u003cbr\u003e\nWhere should I look for that? thanks\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:20.482Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":17,"readers_count":16,"score":3.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":707,"topic_slug":"solved-setting-filtermode-to-nearest-was-sizedivisor","display_username":"Jimmy Gass","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":109,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":3890,"name":"","username":"reattiva","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/r/b77776/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-01-04T13:39:53.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eFrom what I read in the code, FILTER_NEAREST works on both magnification and minification.\u003cbr\u003e\nTry stepping through the code and see what happens in Texture::UpdateParameters when you are creating your buffer.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:21.791Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":17,"readers_count":16,"score":3.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":707,"topic_slug":"solved-setting-filtermode-to-nearest-was-sizedivisor","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":72,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":3899,"name":"Jimmy Gass","username":"ghidra","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/ghidra/{size}/69_2.png","created_at":"2015-01-05T01:23:03.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYeah im not sure what the deal is really. I would take your advice, but that is over my head already. Im just a script pesant.\u003cbr\u003e\nHowever, this code from this answer on stackoverflow seemed to do the trick with some silly modifications:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5879403/opengl-texture-coordinates-in-pixel-space/5879551#5879551\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003ehttp://stackoverflow.com/questions/5879403/opengl-texture-coordinates-in-pixel-space/5879551#5879551\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003evec2 s = (1.0/(cGBufferInvSize.xy))*2.0;\nvec2 new_uv = (2.0*((vScreenPos.xy / vScreenPos.w)*s) + 0.5)/(2.0*s);\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUsing this when sampeling a fullsize buffer to a half sized quad, and it gives me crisp edges again.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:22.621Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":17,"readers_count":16,"score":3.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":707,"topic_slug":"solved-setting-filtermode-to-nearest-was-sizedivisor","display_username":"Jimmy Gass","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5879403/opengl-texture-coordinates-in-pixel-space/5879551#5879551","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"iphone - OpenGL Texture Coordinates in Pixel Space - Stack Overflow","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":109,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"stream":[3850,3873,3874,3876,3890,3899]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,2884],[2,2881],[5,2880],[6,2879]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7067,"title":"Can the latest Urho3D version be built with VS2013?","fancy_title":"Can the latest Urho3D version be built with VS2013?","slug":"can-the-latest-urho3d-version-be-built-with-vs2013","posts_count":3,"reply_count":0,"highest_post_number":3,"image_url":null,"created_at":"2021-11-25T18:00:24.336Z","last_posted_at":"2021-11-26T17:22:21.878Z","bumped":true,"bumped_at":"2021-11-26T17:22:21.878Z","archetype":"regular","unseen":false,"pinned":false,"unpinned":null,"visible":true,"closed":false,"archived":false,"bookmarked":null,"liked":null,"tags_descriptions":{},"like_count":0,"vie